  <body>
    <p>The software event broker  resides in a container that is wrapped within a Linux OS to make an event broker virtual machine image. In its default state, this event broker Linux host environment has remote login disabled and contains no passwords.</p>
    <p>To log in to the event broker for the first time, you must log in as <code>sysadmin</code>, which is the default user account for the Linux host environment. You will be prompted to create a password for that user.</p>
  </body>
</html>
